<paragraph id="894136C3A22F5733FF01F5D1DBE3FCF6" blockId="2.[168,777,405,834]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="BB8AEAD1A22F5733FF01F5D1D8F4FE1A" box="[168,683,405,430]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" reason="1">
<emphasis id="BB8AEAD1A22F5733FF01F5D1DB15FE1A" bold="true" box="[168,330,405,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Identification.</emphasis>
This species is very similar to
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4EFE4D40A22F5733FD1FF5D1D878FE78" authority="Cassola, 2000" authorityName="Cassola" authorityYear="2000" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mindanaoensis">
<emphasis id="BB8AEAD1A22F5733FD1FF5D1DB23FE78" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="BB8AEAD1A22F5733FD1FF5D1DA93FE78" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" reason="1">Calomera</emphasis>
mindanaoensis
</emphasis>
Cassola, 
<quantity id="4E069B26A22F5733FE58F5F3D878FE78" box="[497,551,439,463]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" unit="in" value="2000.0">2000</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in appearance and size, the absence of visible elytra punctuation, and in the labrum with more than 10 marginal setae. However, 
<taxonomicName id="4EFE4D40A22F5733FD59F5BFDB45FD83" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1825" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacrymosa">
<emphasis id="BB8AEAD1A22F5733FD59F5BFDB45FD83" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">C. lacrymosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has elaborate markings on the side compared to 
<taxonomicName id="4EFE4D40A22F5733FF6CF67ADBD7FDE1" authorityName="Cassola" authorityYear="2000" box="[197,392,574,598]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mindanaoensis">
<emphasis id="BB8AEAD1A22F5733FF6CF67ADBD7FDE1" box="[197,392,574,598]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">C. mindanaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both species have their pronotum and elytra metallic green and red in color, but 
<taxonomicName id="4EFE4D40A22F5733FD0FF624DABEFD2E" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1825" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacrymosa">
<emphasis id="BB8AEAD1A22F5733FD0FF624DABEFD2E" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">C. lacrymosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a larger anterior lateral dot, and in that species the discal dot is somewhat connected with a narrow lineole. Moreover, the aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName id="4EFE4D40A22F5733FE54F681D8E0FD6A" authorityName="Cassola" authorityYear="2000" box="[509,703,709,733]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mindanaoensis">
<emphasis id="BB8AEAD1A22F5733FE54F681D8E0FD6A" box="[509,703,709,733]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">C. mindanaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is arcshape and slightly tapering at the apex, but the aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName id="4EFE4D40A22F5733FF6CF74DDB09FC97" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[197,342,776,800]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacrymosa">
<emphasis id="BB8AEAD1A22F5733FF6CF74DDA88FC97" box="[197,215,777,800]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BB8AEAD1A22F5733FF4CF74CDB09FC97" box="[229,342,776,800]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">lacrymosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also arc-shaped but much longer and thinner towards the apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="894136C3A22F5733FF01F717DB6EFC44" blockId="2.[168,775,851,1011]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="BB8AEAD1A22F5733FF01F717DBB5FCDC" bold="true" box="[168,490,851,876]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Endemism and distribution.</emphasis>
An Oriental species; 
<collectingCountry id="F1E97653A22F5733FD7BF710DAA9FC3A" name="Philippines" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Philippines</collectingCountry>
(Luzon, 
<collectingRegion id="4B3AF821A22F5733FECBF731DB9FFC3A" box="[354,448,885,909]" country="Philippines" name="Palawan" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Palawan</collectingRegion>
, Sibuyan, Balabac, Mindoro, Homonhon, Bucas Grande) and 
<collectingCountry id="F1E97653A22F5733FDB2F7D3D8DCFC18" box="[539,643,919,943]" name="Indonesia" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="4B3AF821A22F5733FD3EF7D3D8A4FC18" box="[663,763,919,943]" country="Indonesia" name="Sulawesi Utara" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Sulawesi</collectingRegion>
), although this range is still under investigation (
<bibRefCitation id="ED6F4B32A22F5733FD12F7FDDB79FC44" author="Cabras A &amp; Cabigas E &amp; Wiesner J" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" pagination="188 - 201" refId="ref4783" refString="Cabras A, Cabigas E, Wiesner J (2016 b) Updated checklist of tiger beetles in the Philippines, Coleoptera: Carabidae: Cicindelinae, (131 th contribution towards the knowledge of Cicindelinae). Lambillionea CXVI 3: 188 - 201." type="journal article" year="2016">Cabras et al. 2016b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C1E46548A22F5733FF01F041DEE5FE73" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="894136C3A22F5733FF01F041DEE5FE73" blockId="2.[168,776,1028,1154]" lastBlockId="2.[810,1420,160,452]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="BB8AEAD1A22F5733FF01F041DB48FBAA" bold="true" box="[168,279,1029,1053]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was observed at only one of the nine sites explored. It was found perching on the ground on a sun-exposed road in an agricultural area. It was rather rare in the area. Cassola (2000) gave an excellent historical account of this species and a brief description under the name 
<taxonomicName id="4EFE4D40A22F5733FC4DF486DFD7FF6D" authority="(Dejean, 1825)" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[996,1416,194,218]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Lophyridia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacrymosa">
<emphasis id="BB8AEAD1A22F5733FC4DF486DE86FF6D" box="[996,1241,194,218]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Lophyridia lacrymosa</emphasis>
(Dejean, 1825)
</taxonomicName>
. Later, 
<bibRefCitation id="ED6F4B32A22F5733FCD3F4A7DE43FF4C" author="Cassola F" box="[890,1052,227,251]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" pagination="129 - 131" refId="ref4927" refString="Cassola F (2011) Studies of tiger beetles. CLXXXIX. A new Calomera species from Mindanao, Philippines (Coleoptera, Cicindelidae). Spixiana 34 (1): 129 - 131." type="journal article" year="2011">Cassola (2011)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="4EFE4D40A22F5733FB04F4A7D93BFEAA" authority="Jeannel, 1946" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1946" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Lophyridia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BB8AEAD1A22F5733FB04F4A7DF7AFF4C" box="[1197,1317,227,251]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Lophyridia</emphasis>
Jeannel, 1946
</taxonomicName>
, as junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4EFE4D40A22F5733FBE2F541DFD8FEAA" authority="Motschulsky, 1862" authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1862" box="[1099,1415,261,285]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BB8AEAD1A22F5733FBE2F541DEE9FEAA" box="[1099,1206,261,285]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Calomera</emphasis>
Motschulsky, 1862
</taxonomicName>
, and hence, 
<taxonomicName id="4EFE4D40A22F5733FC0FF563DE6BFE89" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[934,1076,294,318]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Lophyridia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacrymosa">
<emphasis id="BB8AEAD1A22F5733FC0FF563DE6BFE89" box="[934,1076,294,318]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">L. lacrymosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is now 
<taxonomicName id="4EFE4D40A22F5733FB21F562DF46FE89" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[1160,1305,294,318]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Lophyridia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacrymosa">
<emphasis id="BB8AEAD1A22F5733FB21F562DF46FE89" box="[1160,1305,294,318]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">C. lacrymosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species is widespread in the 
<collectingCountry id="F1E97653A22F5733FBE9F503DEE2FEE8" box="[1088,1213,327,351]" name="Philippines" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Philippines</collectingCountry>
, from Luzon south to Mindanao. Cabras et al. (2016) listed several major islands in the distributional range of the species, with a questionable account from Sulawesi.
</paragraph>
